                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18030706-28-off155 t18030706-28-crimeloc158"></join>: On the 28th of May, about one o'clock in the day, I was alarmed by a neighbour, that I was robbed of a carpet from my back yard; I pursued the prisoner, he turned out of the high-street; I got into Pennington-street, and then I saw him with my carpet under his arm; he saw me coming behind him, and he threw it down; I went on and took him, I never lost sight of him, it was my carpet; he said, it was his first offence, and that distress was the cause of it.</p>

               <p>Prisoner's defence. I was running away from a press-gang, I never saw the carpet.</p>

